## 6. Secondary Contributing Factor

### `meanAbsDelta` Quality Penalty May Be Too Aggressive

At [useCPROrchestrator.ts:181](file:///d:/diacom%20demo/Viewers/modes/cpr/src/useCPROrchestrator.ts#L181):
```typescript
score -= Math.min(12, (summary.meanAbsDelta - 520) / 80);
```

For noisy MIP, `meanAbsDelta` (mean of absolute neighbor deltas) will be high, but this penalty is capped at 12 points while MIP-specific penalties don't exist. A dedicated "noise variance" quality metric comparing standard deviation to signal range would better discriminate noisy MIP from clean MEAN outputs.
